description.p:
In the leaning vehicle with a steerable front wheel, according to the embodiment of the present teaching, the centripetal force generation actuator is any one of the following: (a), (b), (c), a combination of (a) and (b), a combination of (a) and (c), a combination of (b) and (c), or a combination of (a), (b) and (c);


(a) a rotating electric machine for steering a steerable wheel that is mechanically connected to the one or two steerable front wheels, rotates its output member in a third direction to apply torque to swivel the one or two steerable front wheels in a fifth direction and rotates its output member in a fourth direction to apply torque to swivel the one or two steerable front wheels in a sixth direction;

(b) a power unit that applies different amounts of torque to the respective wheels of the steerable front wheels or the rear wheels that are formed by a right wheel and a left wheel; and

(c) a brake unit that applies different amounts of torque to the respective wheels of the steerable front wheels or the rear wheels that are formed by a right wheel and a left wheel.

claim.claim-text:
A leaning vehicle with a steerable front wheel, the leaning vehicle comprising:
a vehicle body;
one or two steerable front wheels that are supported by the vehicle body in such a manner so as to be able to swivel around an axis extending in a vehicle-body's up-down direction;
one or two rear wheels that are supported by the vehicle body in such a manner so as to be unable to swivel around an axis extending in the vehicle-body's up-down direction, the number of the rear wheels being two when the number of the steerable front wheels is one, and the number of the rear wheels being one or two when the number of the steerable front wheels is two;
a turn operation input device that receives a turn operation to turn the leaning vehicle by a rider and is configured to not transmit the turn operation mechanically, thereby preventing the one or two steerable front wheels from swiveling due to mechanical transmission of the turn operation;
a leaning device including a lean actuator that leans the vehicle body, the one or two steerable front wheels and the one or two rear wheels to a vehicle's leftward direction when the turn operation inputted to the turn operation input device is a turn operation to turn the leaning vehicle in the vehicle's leftward direction, and leans the vehicle body, the one or two steerable front wheels and the one or two rear wheels to a vehicle's rightward direction when the turn operation inputted to the turn operation input device is a turn operation to turn the leaning vehicle in the vehicle's rightward direction; and
a controller that controls the lean actuator, wherein:
the leaning vehicle further comprises a centripetal force generator including a centripetal force generation actuator that outputs torque that is controllable to generate an additional centripetal force that acts on the one or two steerable front wheels and the one or two rear wheels that are leaning during a turn of the leaning vehicle; and
the controller controls the torque outputted from the centripetal force generation actuator while controlling the lean actuator in accordance with the turn operation inputted to the turn operation input device, and thereby controls the leaning condition of the vehicle body during the turn of the leaning vehicle and the centripetal force acting on the one or two steerable front wheels and the one or two rear wheels during the turn of the leaning vehicle.

The leaning vehicle with a steerable front wheel according to claim 5, wherein the in-motion state detector detects any of the following (1), (2) and (3) as the physical quantity:
(1) a physical quantity relating to the lean angle of the vehicle body;
(2) a physical quantity relating to the vehicle speed of the leaning vehicle with a steerable front wheel; and
(3) a physical quantity relating to the lateral acceleration of the leaning vehicle, which is an acceleration of the vehicle body in a vehicle's left-right direction;
relating to the in-motion state of the leaning vehicle with a steerable front wheel.

The leaning vehicle with a steerable front wheel according to claim 6, wherein;
the in-motion state detector is a lateral acceleration detector that detects the physical quantity relating to the lateral acceleration of the leaning vehicle, which is an acceleration of the vehicle body in a vehicle's left-right direction; and
the controller controls the torque outputted from the centripetal force generation actuator in view of the lateral acceleration detected by the lateral acceleration detector while controlling the lean actuator in accordance with the turn operation inputted to the turn operation input device, and thereby controls the leaning condition of the vehicle body during the turn of the leaning vehicle and the centripetal force acting on the one or two steerable front wheels and the one or two rear wheels during the turn of the leaning vehicle.

The leaning vehicle with a steerable front wheel according to any one of claims 1 to 12, wherein the centripetal force generation actuator is any one of the following: (a), (b), (c), a combination of (a) and (b), a combination of (a) and (c), a combination of (b) and (c), or a combination of (a), (b) and (c);
(a) a rotating electric machine for steering a steerable wheel that is mechanically connected to the one or two steerable front wheels, rotates in a third direction to apply torque to swivel the one or two steerable front wheels in a fifth rotation direction and rotates in a fourth direction to apply torque to swivel the one or two steerable front wheels in a sixth rotation direction;
(b) a power unit that applies different amounts of torque to the respective wheels of the steerable front wheels or the rear wheels that are formed by a left wheel and a right wheel; and
(c) a brake unit that applies different amounts of torque to the respective wheels of the steerable front wheels or the rear wheels that are formed by a left wheel and a right wheel.
